\b \cf0 How to create a TX Autonomous Standalone System:\
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf0 1 - first build an instrument using the TX Modular system, with all needed controls added onto  Interface screens, and save it. Make sure to put equivalent SyncStart and SyncStop buttons onto the interface screens if they're needed since the system buttons won't be shown. \
If you have controls on more than one interface screen then you will need a way to navigate between screens. \
For example, by creating "Next" and "Previous" action buttons on each screen to jump between them, or a row of buttons such as "Screen 1", "Screen 2", etc.\
For an example of interface screens with simple screen jump buttons, see the file  "
\b Four_Live_Loopers
\b0 " in the "
\i\b TX Mod Examples/Larger_Systems
\i0\b0 " folder.\
\
2 - make a new copy of the TX Modular system standalone application (or download one from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.palemoonrising.co.uk"}}{\fldrslt www.palemoonrising.co.uk}}) and rename it.\
\
3 - open the folders inside the standalone in 
\b Finder
\b0  by Command (or right-) clicking and selecting "Show Package Contents". \
\
4 - inside the standalone there is a folder called"
\i\b Contents/Resources/SCClassLibrary/TX Mod Classes/system/TXDefaultSystemData/
\i0\b0 ".  Into this folder, put a copy of the prebuilt TX Modular system you want to use and rename the copied file as: 
\b TXDefaultSystem
\b0 . When the TX Modular System starts and finds the file TXDefaultSystem in this folder, it opens it automatically as a TX Autonomous Standalone System.\
\
5 - make a copy of any external files used by TXDefaultSystem also putting them inside the standalone in the folder "
\i\b Contents/Resources/SCClassLibrary/TX Mod Classes/system/TXDefaultSystemData/
\i0\b0 " . \
Make sure to include all Wav/Aiff files in Loop and Sample Banks used by File Players, Loop Players, Sample Players, Granulators, Convolutions, as well as any Quartz files used by Quartz Players.
\i\b \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural

\b0 \cf0 Please note
\i0  - any external files which aren't placed in the TXDefaultSystemData folder won't be loaded by the system since, unlike the normal TX Modular system, an autonomous system won't look in external folders. This keeps it self-contained.\
